<plot>1946: Agathocles Cypriotis, a World War II leftist partisan, exiles himself to the island of Milos where he takes up the position of managing director at the minerals company "Varytini". 1956: With his first camera, he films the inhabitants of the island and their activities on 8mm colour film. 2006: The films' "stars" watch the footage for the first time and talk about past times and of the misfortunate disposal of Agathocles Cypriotis, their benefactor, who remained a legend in Milos.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?179914</url></doc>
